## Key Findings

- Excel serial date values were not supported by existing date parsing logic.
- The system partially succeeded in the background but failed at the UI layer.
- Missing acceptance criteria existed for:
  - Numeric date handling
  - User-visible error behavior
  - Detail page rendering guarantees
- Observability gaps caused a user-facing failure to surface as a generic 500 error.

---

## Risks Identified

- Users receive no confirmation despite partial success.
- Payment Upload Detail pages become permanently inaccessible.
- QA cannot deterministically validate behavior without clarified acceptance criteria.

---

## Why This Case Matters

This case demonstrates how **unclear requirements**, not just faulty code, can lead to:
- User-visible production errors
- Support escalations
- Data integrity uncertainty

The agent helps prevent these issues by enforcing **testability and clarity before QA execution**.

